   * 2. The max-heap contains the half of the elements with smaller values
   * 3. The min heap contains the half of the elements with bigger values
   * 4. Compare the amount of nodes in the heap
   * 5. If the max-heap has more nodes, then the median is the root of the min-heap
   * 6. If the min-heap has more nodes, then the median is the root of the max-heap
   * 7. If both heaps have same amount of nodes then the median is the average of the roots of both heaps
   */
  
  
  
  
  
